	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>rainwarrior</b> [ Thu Mar 02, 2017 9:16 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Codemasters Roms, Everdrive N8 and a PAL NES.</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The startup buzz is on the noise channel.<br /><br />Every frame it writes $400C twice, once with volume 5, then with volume 0, 44 cycles later.<br /><br />Thus, it creates a very short burst of noise (44 cycles is slightly longer than 1 sample at 44100 Hz) once per frame.<br /><br />I think emulators might amplify the problem slightly due to the difficulty of filtering out this kind of high frequency effect. (Plus it really stands out against the lack of baseline noise.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


